transcript: They now, stretching themselves after sitting so long, and replacing their purses and pocket- books, entered the ballroom. First came Mdrya Dmitrievna and the count, both with merry countenances. The count, with playful cere- mony somewhat in ballet style, offered his bent arm to Marya Dmitrievna. He drew himself up, a smile of debonair gallantry lit up his face, and as soon as the last figure of the ecos- saise was ended, he clapped his hands to the musicians and shouted up to their gallery,
